  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. A screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to rank input parameter influence on construct stiffness and yield force; parameter rankings informed mesh refinement decisions and boundary-condition choices. This qualitative screening confirmed that cortical bone modulus and screw-rod interface friction coefficient are the dominant drivers of QoI variability.",
