    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level of 3 due to single-condition testing per ASTM F1717 protocol; this gap is accepted given medium model influence and medium decision consequence, consistent with the model risk level 3 determination. All three QoIs pass the pre-established E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. The FEA modeling framework is judged sufficiently credible for its intended use in the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
